description:
Zoodle Pizza 🍕
Soaking up all of the fresh summer produce while we can! We went to @easternmarket today to pick up farm fresh produce, most from @fusilierfamilyfarms96. This zucchini noodle pizza puts a healthy spin on plain old pizza and also is super easy to make vegetarian. 

Ingredients:
4 medium-sized zucchini, spiralized
2 eggs, lightly beaten 
2 cups shredded mozzarella, divided
⅓ cup grated parmesan
¼ cup all-purpose flour
2 T. cornmeal
8 oz. pizza sauce
½ cup pepperoni (optional for vegetarian style)
1 ½ t. Kosher salt
2 T. fresh basil for topping (optional)

Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. In a 9x13 baking dish or foil tray, coat with cooking spray. Place spiralized zucchini in a colander with salt and let sit for 15 minutes. Using a paper towel, squeeze excess moisture out of zucchini. In a medium bowl combine the eggs, 1 cup of mozzarella, parmesan, flour, and cornmeal. Add the zoodles and stir. Transfer mixture to baking dish.
Bake zoodles uncovered for 15 minutes. Next, spread pizza sauce on top of zoodles. Add the remaining mozzarella cheese and the pepperoni. Bake for 20 minutes.
Add basil on top and let the pizza rest for at least 10 minutes.
 Enjoy!! Serves 6-8 

#easternmarket #instafood #instarecipe #healthyrecipes #healthyfood #summerrecipes #summercooking #summerveggies #freshproduce #easyrecipes #foodstagram

description:

• 1-2 plums 
• Dark Grade 100% Pure Maple Syrup 🫗

description:
LEMON BROCCOLI PASTA 
This is not a pretty picture, but it was gooood! I had this huge bag of broccoli I had to cook, so I needed to make something where broccoli was the main star. I was nervous for this, but my husband loved it!! Indy loved it too minus the broccoli lol. I left it out for her. 

Ingredients: 
Organic Broccoli florets 
@simpletruth4u organic White beans 
Pasta 
Lemon juice 
Optional: bacon, Parmesan cheese 

Instructions: 
Prep broccoli with olive oil, lemon juice and salt.
Roast broccoli in the oven at 400 degrees for 15/20 mins. 
Boil water for pasta. I used @cappellos gluten free.
Drain pasta, but keep about a cup of pasta water in the pot.
Add a cup of lemon juice, salt, a can of rinsed white beans and olive oil to the left over water to make a sauce. 
Add parm cheese to the above if using it.
Add the pasta back in.
Put broccoli on the plate first, then scoop over the pasta mixture so the sauce gets on the broccoli too. 
Add some crumbled bacon on top if you want. You can definitely leave the bacon off. It was still very good w out it. 
Enjoy!

description:
Homemade apple pie DONUTS with maple GLAZE HOLY COW 🍎🍩 do not wait to make these… you deserve them this instant! 

DONUT RECIPE
1 3/4 c. flour 
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp baking powder 
2 tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp salt 
2 Tbs butter, melted
1 egg, room temperature 
1/2 c. brown sugar 
1/2 c. granulate sugar 
1/2 c. milk 
1/4 c. apple cider, room temperature 

CRUMB MIXTURE RECIPE 
1/4 c. flour
1/4 c. sugar 
3 Tbs. butter, softened 
Sprinkle of cinnamon 

MAPLE GLAZE RECIPE
1 Tbs butter 
1/4 c. pure maple syrup 
3/4-1 c. powdered sugar 
Pinch of salt and cinnamon 

Whisk together dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. In a separate bowl whisk together remaining (wet) ingredients. Pour dry ingredients into wet ingredients and whisk until just combined. Pour into well greased donut pan, about halfway. 

Cut crumb mixture ingredients together with a fork until crumbles form. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top. Bake at 350 for 10-11 minutes. 

In a small saucepan, melt syrup and butter together. Once melted, remove from heat and whisk in cinnamon, salt, and powdered sugar. Let it rest for a few minutes before drizzling on top of donuts.

description:
SIMPLE ICED MATCHA LATTE 🍵 

THE best summer drink and perfect for those HOT summer days! 🥵

Ingredients: 
1-2 tsp matcha powder (more or less, your preference) 
Milk of choice 
2 tbsp boiling water
Sweetener of choice: stevia, maple syrup, Manuka honey
1 cup of ice

Directions:
In a small bowl, add the matcha powder. Pour in the hot water and whisk until the matcha has fully incorporated into the water. It should be bubbly with no clumps! 

Add ice to a cup. Pour matcha mixture over ice. Add your milk, and sweetener of choice. 

If you have a milk frother, frothing the milk and adding your sweetener then works amazing as well! 

Matcha is high in antioxidants, which help our bodies fight against free radicals that can damage our cells and cause diseases. It also contains vitamin C, selenium, chromium, zinc and magnesium! ✨

LOVE your live, MOVE your body, NOURISH your soul 🌱. 

Recipe by: @nourish.withnicole

description:
Spicy Cucumber Salad, Blue Ribbon Sushi Style 

For those of you who don’t know me, I LOVE @blueribbonsushi LOVE! LOVE! LOVE! I moved to New York City in 1998. I was 18 & starting university. After I graduated my first apt was around the corner from the original Blue Ribbon Sushi on Sullivan Street in SoHo. I thought I was so cool, 22 & living alone in SoHo. Real SJP Carrie Bradshaw sh*t goin’ down. I use to go to Blue Ribbon all the time. Dine alone at the bar, read my book or magazine, & I had a crush on the manager Bowie.💚

So here is a shout out to ALL @eatblueribbon restaurants. The Brasserie down the street, the bakery that once was & now all the locations in all the cities. So many great memories & ALWAYS the BEST food. Anyway, enough of my memory lane BS. Truth be told, I ate there the other night, hence the need to recreate this salad that is, yup you guessed it, simple & delicious.🥒🍋🤍

Takeaway, you too can make this. I sub yuzu hot sauce from @traderjoes for thier garlic & habanero sauce & it’s spot on! 

Ingredients:
5 Persian cucumbers, peeled & sliced round 
¼ cup sour cream
2½ tbsp yuzu hot sauce 
Chives, finely chopped
Flaky salt

Directions:
Place your cucumbers in a bowl & set aside. In a small bowl whisk your sour cream, yuzu hot sauce & salt. Then pour over your cucumbers & stir to evenly coat. Add salt to taste, sprinkle your chives on top & serve. 

PS Little Tip(s)… Little Trick(s)…
•If you want to make more, double the recipe.
•You can use scallions instead of chives.
•You can add minced garlic for an extra kick of flavor. 
•Most importantly, do not be afraid to try new things, even if it seems scary or unattainable, if you put your mind to it you can do it… trust me I’m livin’ proof.💥💛

description:
DOMINOS FAKEAWAY 
• 462 calories inc dip! 

I was kindly sent the @justspices_uk herb dip & I knew instantly it was time to do a two dough ingredient stuffed crust pizza 😋

Ingredients:
• 72g self raising flour 
• 1 light babybel 
• 85g Greek yoghurt (fat free / pizza)
• 10g tomato & basil sauce 
• 14g mozzarella 
• 0.5tsp spicy pizza seasoning 
• 1tsp herb dip seasoning 
• 25g fat free Greek yoghurt 

🎥 reel coming soon

Method ⬇️
• combine your Greek yoghurt & self raising flour into a ball, then lay out into your pizza shape.
• cut up your babybel and place round the edges of the pizza and then fold over so you can no longer see cheese
• spray in frylight & pop into airfryer for 5 mins @ 180c
• after 5 mins add your tomato sauce, pizza seasoning & cheese & pop in for a further 8-10 mins 
• meanwhile make your dip by combining 1tsp of herb seasoning with 25g yoghurt (or to own liking) 

If you want £5 off you can use my discount code justhansfoodsta on just spices website

description:
Dhal - a dish made with lentils or other split pulses ⁠
⁠
Probably one of the simplest Indian dishes you  can cook and healthy and cheap too! ⁠
⁠
Lentils are high in fibre, and complex carbohydrates, while low in fat and calories. Their high protein, gluten free whicht makes them a perfect option for those on a low carb diet. ⁠
⁠
This recipe is my go to, and I often change the type of lentils which gives a different texture and flavour to the dish.⁠
⁠
Rayeesa’s Dhal ⁠
⁠
Ingredients:-⁠
⁠
1cup Red split lentils ⁠
½ med onion thinly sliced⁠
2/3 tbsp. ghee (or ½ veg oil + butter) to fry onions ⁠
1 tsp. turmeric ⁠
1tsp. Paprika ⁠
2 tbsp. Garlic and ginger paste⁠
1 ½ tsp Ground coriander ⁠
Salt to taste⁠
Green chillies, 2 small ones chopped (optional)⁠
Fresh coriander to garnish⁠
⁠
Method :-⁠
⁠
Wash lentils thoroughly in clean water⁠
(Leave to soak for ½ hr if possible)⁠
add turmeric and enough water to cover lentils with approx. 1“ above water⁠
Bring to boil and then let it simmer until lentils are cooked and soft.⁠
Get a masher to mash the lentils or a large spoon.⁠
Add 1 cup water, Green chillies, Paprika, Salt, Ground coriander, Garlic & ginger⁠
Let pan simmer for 5-10mins⁠
Gently fry onions in oil & butter until golden brown and add to dhal mixture⁠
Garnish with fresh coriander and serve!⁠
⁠
#dhal #comfortfood

description:
EASY BAKED ZITI

Ingredients:
- 2 boxes of rigatoni noodles
- 1 container of ricotta, whole milk
- 1 block of mozzarella cheese, freshly grated
- 1 roll of @jimmydean regular (or spicy) sausage
- 2 jars of tomato basil sauce (using @classico_sauce here)
- 1/2 tablespoon of dried basil
- 1/2 tablespoon of garlic powder
- 1/2 tablespoon of Italian seasoning 

Steps:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
2. In a medium to large pot cook your sausage throughly, add your sauce and seasonings and simmer for 20 minutes
3. In another large pot cook your pasta noodles, adding a decent amount of salt and oil while boiling 
4. Drain the noodles and combine with the sauce, stir 
5. Add ricotta cheese and stir well until everything is creamy and well combined
6. Pour into a baking dish and top with mozzarella cheese 
7. Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly

description:
This Porridge with Pistachio and Chia recipe is a #HubSquad submission from one of our lovely members! It is a warming and spicy whole food-based meal. We suggested increasing the serving size of the oats and milk if you’re after a more filling brekkie – this makes it more aligned to The Plate Model, with 1 serve carbohydrate and 1 serve protein. Adding some fruit such as fresh or frozen berries is also a great way to get a serve of fruit whilst adding a bit of sweetness!

Ingredients:
1 cup oats, rolled
500ml milk, any
1 tbsp chia seeds
½ tsp cardamom seeds
20g pistachios, chopped

Method:
1. Place all ingredients in a pan and bring it to the boil.
2. Reduce the heat and let it simmer for 6-8 minutes, stirring occasionally until the porridge is thick and creamy.
3. Serve as is or top with fresh berries for a serving of fruit. We've topped ours with raspberry compote, which is raspberries, water and 1 tsp sugar simmered over the stove until it thickens.

#thehubsquad #dietitian #nutritionist #loseweight #recipes #recipeideas #healthyrecipes #easyrecipes #healthy #health #australia #wholefoods #fruit #healthylifestyle #healthyfoodnj #wholefoods #nutrition #healthyeatinghub

description:
🫕𝗪𝗘𝗟𝗟𝗡𝗘𝗦𝗦 𝗪𝗘𝗗𝗡𝗘𝗦𝗗𝗔𝗬 𝗥𝗘𝗖𝗜𝗣𝗘!!

‼️ 𝗪𝗔𝗥𝗡𝗜𝗡𝗚 - This is 𝘕𝘖𝘛 your 'average' soup recipe!

💚 This recipe was adapted from a recipe featured in the August 'delicious' magazine. Something I LOVE doing, is adapting recipes into a healthy, balanced meal. I adapted this recipe by adding chicken for protein, more veggies and omitting the parmesan to serve, although this is also fine if you choose to add it. 

🍲 💡Healthy food DOES NOT have to be tastless or boring. Remember that recipes can be adapted to become a healthy option. The flavours in this soup were absolutely mouth watering! 

👇

🍗 𝗖𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗻, 𝗖𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗶 𝗕𝗲𝗮𝗻 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗩𝗲𝗴 𝗦𝗼𝘂𝗽

✴️INGREDIENTS:
1 tbsp olive oil
1 leek, finely sliced
1/2 fennel bulb, thinly sliced
3 garlic cloves, crushed
1/2 tsp fennel seeds
6 sprigs oregano, or 1 1/2 tsp dried leaves
1 parmesan rind (such a genius way of adding flavour without the fat and calories of cheese)
4 cups chicken or veg stock
500g chicken breast, cut into large pieces
400g cannellini beans, drained
1 zucchini, diced
2 sticks celery, chopped
1/2 bunch silverbeet

🍋𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘀𝗹𝗲𝘆, 𝗔𝗹𝗺𝗼𝗻𝗱 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗟𝗲𝗺𝗼𝗻 𝗦𝗮𝗹𝘀𝗮 (optional but super delicious and you only need a tsp or two)
40g almonds, toasted
1/4 bunch flat leaf parsley
2 sprigs oregano, or 1/2 tsp dried leaves
juice of 1/2 lemon
40mL olive oil

✴️METHOD:
1️⃣ Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat. Add leek, fennel, celery, garlic, fennel seeds and oregano and cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes until softened and lightly golden.

2️⃣ Season, add parmesan rind, stock and 1 cup water and bring to a simmer. Add chicken pieces and cook for 10 minutes or until chicken is just cooked through.

3️⃣ Remove chicken pieces and allow to cool slightly. Add zucchini, cannelini beans and silverbeet and stir for 3-4 minutes or until zucchini is just softened. Shred chicken, return to saucepan and stir. 

4️⃣ Meanwhile for the salsa, simply blend together all ingredients in thermomix or food processor.

5️⃣ Remove parmesan rind and serve. Top with salsa if using, and fresh, torn parsley leaves. 😋

 this recipe was adapted from a recipe featured in the august 'delicious' magazine. something i love doing, is adapting recipes into a healthy, balanced meal. i adapted this recipe by adding chicken for protein, more veggies and omitting the parmesan to serve, although this is also fine if you choose to add it. 

 healthy food does not have to be tastless or boring. remember that recipes can be adapted to become a healthy option. the flavours in this soup were absolutely mouth watering! 



 𝗖𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗻, 𝗖𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗶 𝗕𝗲𝗮𝗻 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗩𝗲𝗴 𝗦𝗼𝘂𝗽

ingredients:
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 leek, finely sliced
1/2 fennel bulb, thinly sliced
3 garlic clove, crushed
1/2 teaspoon fennel seeds
6 sprig oregano, or 1 1 /2 teaspoon dried leaves
1 parmesan rind (such a genius way of adding flavour without the fat and calories of cheese)
4 cup chicken or veg stock
500 gram chicken breast, cut into large piece
400 gram cannellini beans, drained
1 zucchini, diced
2 stick celery, chopped
1/2 bunch silverbeet

𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘀𝗹𝗲𝘆, 𝗔𝗹𝗺𝗼𝗻𝗱 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗟𝗲𝗺𝗼𝗻 𝗦𝗮𝗹𝘀𝗮 (optional but super delicious and you only need a teaspoon or two)
40 gram almonds, toasted
1/4 bunch flat leaf parsley
2 sprig oregano, or 1/2 teaspoon dried leaves
juice of 1/2 lemon
40 ml olive oil

method:
 heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat. add leek, fennel, celery, garlic, fennel seeds and oregano and cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes until softened and lightly golden.

 season, add parmesan rind, stock and 1 cup water and bring to a simmer. add chicken piece and cook for 10 minutes or until chicken is just cooked through.

 remove chicken piece and allow to cool slightly. add zucchini, cannelini beans and silverbeet and stir for 3-4 minutes or until zucchini is just softened. shred chicken, return to saucepan and stir. 

 meanwhile for the salsa, simply blend together all ingredients in thermomix or food processor.

 remove parmesan rind and serve. top with salsa if using, and fresh, torn parsley leaves.

description:
Save my favorite summer dessert --
🍓Strawberry pudding 🍓

As much as I don't want to admit it--summer is coming to an end but if you're looking for a dessert to bring to the end of the summer parties, you gotta try this one! I love how light it is and that it's no bake! 

Strawberry Pudding

Ingredients:
1 quart strawberries, washed and drained (Plus extra for garnish)
1 package Cream Cheese at room temperature, 8 oz.
2 containers Whipped Topping 8 oz. each (divided)
1 package Vanilla Wafers
1 package instant vanilla pudding
2 1⁄2 cups Milk- enough for pudding recipe.

Directions:
1.In a large bowl slice strawberries. In another bowl mix one container of whipped topping with cream cheese. Mix and set aside for later use.
2. In another bowl combine ingredients for vanilla pudding.
3. Layer bottom of 9x12" glass container with vanilla wafers. Next, layer strawberries, cool whip & cream cheese mixture, then pudding.
4.Top with whipped topping and garnish with extra strawberries

Save this recipe for your next party! 

Share your favorite summer dessert in the comments!!

description:
What could be better in summer than a BBQ with your favorite people? 🥳 We've brought you a particularly cool recipe idea for this: Pulled Pork Carnitas with our homemade Sour Cream Sauce! 🌮🍻

Ingredients:
- 250 g Sour Cream
- 100 g Mayonnaise (min. 50% fat)
- 100 g Cream Cheese
- 50 g Yogurt 3.2%
- ½ tsp Smoked Paprika Powder
- ½ tsp Chili Cayenne
- 1 tsp Ground Cumin
- ½ tsp Garlic Powder
- 1 tbsp Dried Oregano
- Juice of 1/4 Lime
- Salt & Pepper

Preparation:
1️⃣ Blend all ingredients finely with a hand blender or in a stand mixer.
Then pour the entire mixture through iSi Funnel & Sieve into a 0.5 L iSi Whip. Screw on an iSi Professional Charger and shake vigorously 12-14 times.

description:
SAUSAGE, MUSHROOM & BRIE EGG BAKE

INGREDIENTS:
- 16 oz mild Italian sausage
- 2 cups mushroom (sliced)
- 1 small red onion (diced)
- 1 clove minced garlic
- 4 cups spinach
- 1 cup brie cheese (cubed)
- 10 eggs
- 1/2 cup milk
- 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1 1/2 tsp onion powder
- 1 tsp green goddess seasoning (can omit)
- salt
- pepper
- 1 can crescent roll

STEPS:
1. Start by preheating the oven to 350 degrees.  While the oven is preheating, brown the sausage, slice the mushrooms, and dice the onion.
2. Once the sausage is done, set aside and add the mushroom, onion, and garlic to the pan with the grease from the sausage.  Stir frequently until it is all soft and fragrant, then add in the spinach until it is wilted.  Set aside.
3. Next dice up the brie cheese into cubes and also set aside.  Grab a medium sized bowl and add the eggs, milk, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper, and green goddess seasoning.  Mix until well combined.
4. Once everything is has been prepped it’s time to assemble the bake.  Start by adding the crescent roll to the base layer of a 9 x 12 baking dish.  Next follow with the browned sausage, the sautéed veggies, and the brie cheese.  Finally top it all with the egg mixture.
5. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean in the middle.  Serve with avocado and your favorite hot sauce!

Enjoy! ✨

description:
Who doesn’t love a recipe that is simple and delicious? 💁🏻‍♀️

I make this once a week - it’s enough for dinner 2 nights in a row and both of our kiddos *love* it! 😋

Ingredients:
•2 Lbs Ground Beef (we use 85/15)
•2 Medium Zucchini (sliced & quartered)
•Elbow Pasta (8oz - I use @eatbanza because it’s gluten free -plus it adds more fiber & protein!)
•Tomato Sauce (8oz)
•Chicken Broth (4 Cups)
•Shredded Cheddar Cheese (1 Cup)
•Mustard (2T)
•Hamburger Seasoning (1T)
•Tobasco (Optional - to taste)
•Salt + Pepper (to taste)

How to Make It:
•pan fry ground beef in a large pot/skillet
•when beef is finished, toss in the zucchini
•once the zucchini is somewhat tender - add in the broth, pasta, tomato sauce, mustard, tobasco & seasonings. 
•simmer until pasta is ready, then fold in the cheese #ewdavid (IYKYK 😂)

Makes 6 servings (1 serving is roughly 466 grams)

*Swipe for Nutrition Facts*

Make sure you save this post, follow me for more recipes and comment below if you try this 😍

JOY!
-HP

description:
Lentil & Meatball Soup With Veggies 🧆🍲 

Ingredients: 
-1 1/2 Cup Lentils
-1.5 Lb of Ground Beef
-1 Onion 
-1 Large Carrot
-2 Large Celery Sticks
-1/2 Tsp Curry
-1/4 Tsp Turmeric
-1 Tsp Aleppo Pepper
-2 1/2 Tsp Dry Dill
-1/4 Tsp Garlic Powder
-1 1/2 Tbsp Tomato Paste
-1 Egg
-Salt and Pepper to Taste

Preparation: 
Begin by chopping half the onion into very small pieces or grinding it. Start mixing the ground beef, dry ingredients, tomato paste, egg and onion. Boil a pot of water and once it starts bubbling start rolling up the meatballs and throw them in(You can make them as big or small as you want). While the meatballs begin to cook, poor the lentils into a pot and pour water just enough to cover the lentils. Once the meatballs are about more than half way cooked remove them from the pot and keep them on the side. The lentils should also be cooked by this time but you can always check to see. Rinse the lentils. In a different pot add a bit of any kind of oil you prefer and dice the other half of the onion and begin to sauté it. Dice the celery and carrots and add it to the onion and sauté together. Once they begin to cook a little , add in the lentils and meatballs and mix. Add about 4-5 cups of boiling water, mix. Season the soup with salt and pepper to your taste, let it come to a simmer and it is ready to be eaten. Enjoy!

description:
Kick your immunity into gear with this easy to make Onion and Chicken Soup 🤤 Packed full of immune-boosting nutrients, you'll want to sip on this all month long! 

Get the recipe from @kitchenofyouth below 👇

Ingredients:
2 large onions, chopped
4 spring onions, sliced (be sure to also add the root ends to the soup -- they are extra healing)
2 large carrots, peeled and sliced
3 celery stalks, sliced
12 large garlic cloves, smashed
4 large sticks of wakame seaweed (this can be left out, or replaced with spinach)
1/4 cup chicken bone broth (this can be substituted with chicken stock)
3 cups water
500g boneless chicken thighs, cut into 1-inch pieces
Salt and pepper, to taste
1 cup small pasta

Method:
1. Put all of the ingredients, except the pasta, into a slow cooker.
2. Cook on high for 4-hours.
3. Add pasta and cook for an additional 15 mins or until the pasta is cooked al dente.

NOTE: This soup can be made on top of the stove if you prefer. Follow the directions above, but you will probably only need to cook the soup for about 1-1/2 hours. Then add the pasta until cooked al dente.

4 large stick of wakame seaweed (this can be left out, or replaced with spinach)
1/4 cup chicken bone broth (this can be substituted with chicken stock)
3 cup water
500 gram boneless chicken thighs, cut into 1 -inch piece
salt and pepper, to taste
1 cup small pasta

method:
1 . put all of the ingredients, except the pasta, into a slow cooker.
2 . cook on high for 4 -hours.
3 . add pasta and cook for an additional 15 mins or until the pasta is cooked al dente.

note: this soup can be made on top of the stove if you prefer. follow the directions above, but you will probably only need to cook the soup for about 1-1 /2 hours. then add the pasta until cooked al dente.

description:
I keep coming back to my Sausage ‘risotto’ for many reasons, it’s quick, delicious, and full of low carb veg and meat. Good thing I love this dish because I’ll be eating it all week 😅
Since I’m pregnant I’m adding peas, but if you’re strict Keto you can easily substitute these for broccoli, or leave them out all together 
.
.
.

.
.
Ingredients: 
2 tbsp butter 
1 tbsp olive oil 
Meat of 6 sausages, removed from the skin
1 onion, diced 
1 bell pepper, diced 
1/2 tsp chili flakes 
1 tsp Italian Herbs 
2 garlic cloves, minced 
250g cauliflower rice 
100g frozen peas 
150g grated mozzarella cheese 
.
.
.
.
Directions: 
1️⃣Heat the butter and oil on medium high, until hot. Add the sausage meat and brown 
2️⃣Add the onion and pepper, cook until soft 
3️⃣Turn the heat down to low. Add the chili, Italian herbs, and garlic; cook until fragrant 
4️⃣Add the cauliflower and peas. Cook until the peas are warmed through 
5️⃣Mix through the mozzarella. Enjoy! 
.
.
.
.
Nutritional Info: serves 4
Calories: 523
Carbs: 10.7g
Fat: 41.3g
Protein: 24.9g 
.
.

.
.
.
.

description:
Are you Ready for the Air Fryer Revolution?

The first thing you need to know about air fryers is that they don’t actually fry things. Once you place your food in the frying basket, the machine blows hot air to create a convection cooking effect that browns the food. The crunchy texture is similar to what you would achieve by deep frying.

If you Running out the door to be next in line to buy an Air Fryer or already own one, here is a super easy, delicious chicken recipe to try. 
Tender and Juicy Air Fryer Chicken is golden crispy outside and moist and delicate on the inside. 
Bursting with flavor and oh so good! 

Prep Time: 10 mins
Cook Time: 18 mins

Ingredients:
2 skinless chicken breasts
1 Tablespoons olive oil
1 Tablespoon Italian seasoning
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon paprika
Salt and Pepper
Optional: Vegetables (brussel sprouts, carrots, green beans)

Method:
Place the chicken in the air fryer basket. Rub olive oil on the chicken.
In a small bowl add the Italian seasoning, garlic powder, paprika, salt and pepper. Rub on each sides of the chicken.
Cook in the air fryer at 200 degrees for 9 minutes. Open the air fryer and flip the chicken. 
Add the vegetables at this point if using. 
Cook for another 9 minutes or until chicken is done.
Enjoy with some spicy rice or garlic rolls.

Stay tuned for more in our Recipe series…
To View Previous Recipes, Download the Crescent Lifestyle APP and find them on the Social Timeline: http://bit.ly/CresLife

description:
Thai Kale Cashew Salad with Lemon-Ginger Vinaigrette 🥙

Servings: 4
Calories 320, 25g carb, 20g fat, 10g protein.

Ingredients:

Dressing

3 Tbsp. sesame or coconut oil
2 Tbsp. coconut aminos or low-sodium soy sauce
1 Tbsp. raw apple cider vinegar
1/2 tsp. fish sauce
1 tsp. minced fresh ginger
1 large clove garlic, peeled and minced
1.5 tsp. lemongrass paste

Salad

1/8 tsp. sea salt
6 cups kale, chopped (if you don’t have kale, then you can use romaine lettuce or spinach)
1/2-3/4 medium carrot, peeled and shredded or julienned
1/2 cup shredded red cabbage, very thinly sliced
1/2-1 bell pepper (red or yellow), thinly sliced
1 green onion, thinly sliced
3 Tbsp fresh cilantro leaves, chopped
1/4 cup dry roasted cashews, chopped
Lime wedges for garnish

INSTRUCTIONS

Combine dressing ingredients in a small bowl and whisk well to combine. Set aside.
Place kale in a large bowl and sprinkle with sea salt. Using your hands, massage the kale with a kneading motion until leaves start to wilt and become slightly shiny or wet-looking (about 2-3 minutes). Very important to massage the kale this way! It makes it more tender and less bitter.
Add carrots through cilantro, then pour dressing over all. Toss to combine.
Garnish with chopped cashews just before serving. Serve with lime wedges.

description:
The perfect picnic basket filler. Full recipe below 👇

Ingredients:
- 50g butter
- 6 spring onions, sliced
- 200g jumbo oats
- 150g grated carrot
- 50g almonds, roughly chopped
- 3tbsp mixed seeds, divided
- 150g Dubliner Lighter, grated
- 2 eggs, beaten
- 1/2 tsp salt flakes
- 1/4 tsp black pepper

Method:
1️⃣Pre-heat oven to 200°C/180°C fan/gas 6 and line a 20cm (8 inches) square tin with baking paper. Set aside.
2️⃣In a large mixing bowl, combine the oats, carrot, almonds, grated Dubliner Lighter cheese, salt, pepper, and 2tsp of the mixed seeds. Mix well with a large spoon.
3️⃣Melt the butter in a small saucepan over medium heat, then add the spring onion and cook until butter starts to foam and spring onion softens. Remove from the heat and stir into the dry mixture. Add the beaten eggs and mix well until evenly combined.
4️⃣Tip mixture into the prepared tin, pressing down evenly with the back of a large spoon or spatula. Scatter with the remaining 1 tbsp of the seeds on the top.
5️⃣Bake for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Cook in the tin for 10 minutes, then use the paper to lift the flapjack out onto a wire rack to cool completely.
6️⃣Use a bread knife to cut flapjacks into your preferred-sized portions.

#DistinctivelyDubliner #DublinerCheese #Cheese #CheeseLover #RecipeIdeas #FlapJacks #Summer #Picnics #SummerPicnics #FamilyPicnics #FamilyDayOut

description:
* RECIPE POST 

Some days you want to indulge in rich, restaurant-like North-Indian food but then you don’t want to indulge in the cooking that it calls for! Nahi? 😂

This ‘Paneer in Cashew & Mawa Gravy’ is the answer to your dilemma! It’s quick to cook, takes less amount of preps and the outcome? 🤤 Words can’t describe it! You’ll know when you try it!

Some hot sizzling rotis to go with it, and you’re good to go! 

Here is the recipe: (perfect for the festive season) 

Ingredients:

Paneer 250 grams
Onion 1 medium chopped
Garlic 3-4 cloves chopped
Cashews 15 pcs
Mawa 100 grams grated (50 + 50) 
Cardamom 2 pc whole
Cinnamon stick 1
Cloves 2
Pepper corns 7-8 pcs
Cumin seeds 1 tsp
Tej patta 1
Milk 1/2 cup
Yogurt 1 tbsp
Garam masala 1 tsp (or kitchen king masala)
Salt to taste
Fresh Cream 2 tbsp
Oil
Ghee

Method:

Step 1: 

Take oil in a pan. Add the whole spices (cardamom, peppercorn, cloves, cinnamon) and sauté garlic and onion in this until soft. Cool down.

Important: Discard the cinnamon. 

Blend into a smooth gravy along with 50 grams Mawa and 15 cashews and a little water. 

Step 2: 

Take ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds and tej patta. Sauté and add the gravy. Cook for 3-4 minutes before adding 1/2 cup milk and grated Mawa (this part of the Mawa is optional) Again cool for 4-5 minutes on low heat and then add 1 tbsp yogurt. 

Keep cooking while adding the salt and garam masala. Now add the cream and the paneer and cook for 2 minutes. Switch off and serve immediately.

(The gravy thickens as it cools down, so if you want you can add milk and cook a little to reach the desired consistency!)

Do try and let me know in the comments how you like it!! ❤️

#paneerrecipes #paneer #paneerlover #recipeoftheday #recipeideas #festiverecipes #festiveseason #festivevibes #foodphotography #eeeeats #northindianfood #simplerecipes #easyrecipesathome #cottagecheeserecipes

11. Ginger Paste 1 tbsp
12. Coriander Powder 1 tsp 
13. Cumin Powder 1 tsp
14. Chicken 300 gm
15. Cashew paste 4 tbsp
16. Salt to taste
17. Green Chili 8-10 pcs 
18. Water 1.5 cup

Instructions: 

1. Blend bread with warm milk.
2. In a pot, add cooking oil, clarified butter, bay leaf, cinnamon sticks, cardamom, cloves, onion paste, garlic paste, ginger paste, coriander powder, cumin powder, and sauté for 2-3 minutes.
3. Add chicken and sauté for 5-6 minutes. 
4. Add cashew paste, salt, green chili, and sauté for 5 minutes.
5. Pour the bread milk and sauté for another 5 minutes.
6. Add warm milk, water and cook for 20 minutes. 

Ready to Enjoy!

description:
How about
Creamy Mushroom  Chicken Alfredo for dinner
This was so easy to make and it tastes amazing!
Ingredients:
2 skinless chicken breasts, diced
450g fettuccine noodles
2-1/2 cups all purpose cream/whipping cream
5 cloves garlic, minced
1 sm onion, chopped
1 cup champignons/canned mushrooms, optional
1-1/2 cups shredded parmessan cheese
2 tbs butter
salt and white pepper to taste
1/2 tsp ground nutmeg, optional
1 tbs oregano
Method:
Cook fettucine according to package instructions and set aside.
In a large skillet, saute chicken in 1-1/2 tbs cooking oil.
Cook until no longer pink and juices run clear.
Remove and keep warm.
In the same skillet, saute garlic and onions until tender.
Add the champignons/mushrooms and cook for 3-5minutes.
Add butter, salt and pepper, all purpose cream and cheese.
Return chicken to the pan; heat through and until the cheese is melted.
Serve Alfredo sauce over prepared noodles.
Garnished with freshly grated parmesan and parsley if desired.
 enjoy

description:
Strawberry Custard Slices 🧁🍰🍓

Makes 8
Ingredients:
Jus rol or any brand of pre rolled puff pastry 
250g double or whipping cream
200g ready made custard
Icing sugar
Strawberries halved
 
Method:
Cut the pastry into 8 even slices and bake according to the packets instructions. 
To make the filling whip the cream until it is thick and doesn't drop, then fold in the custard and mix together. Put it in the fridge.
When the pastry is fully cooled cut them in half. Spead a good layer of custard cream over the bottom half of the pastry and place a few strawberries over the cream. Then add the top half of the pastry and dust with icing sugar in a sieve. You can whip some extra cream and put a dollop on top of the finished pastry with a strawberry on top if you like.

description:
Greek Chicken Kebabs 🍗🧅🍅🫓

Serves 2
Ingredients:
4 tbsp olive oil divided 
2 tbsp freshly squeezed lemon juice 
1 tbsp lemon zest (optional)
1 tsp paprika
2 tsp dried oregano
2 tsp dried basil
1 tsp dried thyme
3 cloves garlic minced
1 shallot minced
Sea Salt and freshly ground black Pepper 
2lb boneless and skinless chicken thighs cut into one inch chunks
1 red onion
1 red pepper
10 cherry tomatoes halved

Method:
In a large bowl mix 2 tbsp olive oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, paprika, oregano, basil, thyme, garlic, shallot, 1 tsp salt and 1 tsp pepper. Stir in the chicken and mix it well. Leave for at least 2 hours but preferably leave overnight.

Thread the chicken onto the skewers. Brush on each side with the extra 2 tbsp olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Grill or bbq them. I chose to bbq them, they can be grilled on medium heat. Turn them though out cooking either way you cook them. 

I combined chopped red onion, chopped red pepper and cherry tomatoes and olive oil and salt and ppper and cooked them on the bbq in a bbq wok. Serve immediately with hummus or tzatziki sauce and heated pitta breads. I used @dunnesstores lemon and coriander hummus.

description:
Mutton chops with gravy

Ingredients:
600g mutton or lamb chops (about 8 chops)
6 green chillies
4 red chillies
3 slices ginger (each 1cm or in thick)
5 cloves garlic
2 tbsp plain yoghurt or juice of 1 lime
2 tbsp coriander (ketumbar) powder
1 tbsp chilli powder
2 onions-chop
4 tomatoes - chop
6 stalks coriander leaves - chop
salt to taste

Ingredients for frying
1 small onion - slice thinly
4 cardamoms
5 cloves
1 stick cinnamon 5cm (2 in) long
10 tbsp oil

4 cups water

Method:
Blend the green chillies, red chillies, ginger and garlic
In a large bowl, combine chops with all the ingredients except ingredients for frying, oil and water. Heat oil, add
ingredients for frying. When fragrant, add mutton and fry till fragrant then add water. Cover and boil, removing cover and stirring from time to time. Continue cooking till mutton is tender and the gravy is very thick.

description:
Ratatouille 

A comforting, warm dish to make with summer veggies to enjoy right away, or freeze for later. My mother in law taught me how to make ratatouille during summer months in Brittany. No recipe needed! 

Ingredients: 
-Onion, garlic
-Tomatoes
-Zucchini 
-Bell peppers 
-Fresh herbs and dried spices: thyme, basil, oregano, rosemary, parsley 

You can also add summer squash or eggplant. Sauté onion and garlic in olive oil. Simmer everything in a large pot until flavorful and vegetables are soft. Serve as a side with anything: fish, meat, or rice.

description:
We’ve turned International Beer Day into a weekend, and it calls for something more than cracking open a cold one.

Make your boozy weekend a little more exciting, with Aunty D’s Crispy Beer Battered Chicken recipe! It’s quick, simple and deliciously addictive!

Ingredients:

Chicken 400 g
Garlic Powder 1 tsp
Pepper ¾ tsp
Salt 1 ¼ tsp
All-purpose Flour ½ cup
Cornflour ½ cup
Chilli Powder 1 tsp
Turmeric ¼ tsp
Beer ¾ cups

Method:

To a bowl, add the prepped chicken cuts, garlic powder, pepper and salt, mix and let it marinate for 30 minutes.

Combine all-purpose flour, cornflour, chilli powder, turmeric and beer in a separate bowl and whisk until it forms a smooth batter. 

Dip the marinated chicken in the batter and fry them in oil until golden on all sides.

Serve while it’s hot!

description:
Potato - mushroom scones with cheese and green onion feathers
For a long time, I wanted to make something like this to show once again that we can eat potatoes, and this does not harm our weight.

Ingredients:
🔸1 Egg
🔸500 g Potatoes (fresh, peeled)
🔸150 g Mushrooms (champignons)
🔸 40 g Flour (I use corn flour)
🔸 40 g Onion green feather
 🔸90 g Processed cheese (3x 30 g)
🔸 8 g Oil
🔸 Salt, pepper

Preparation:
1 Peel the potatoes and cook until they are soft. Drain the excess water and grind/blend them into a porridge. Cool it.

2 Finely chop the mushrooms and fry in a pan with spices.

3 To the cooled potato porridge - add eggs, onion, flour, salt, pepper, and fried mushrooms at the end, and knead a homogeneous dough. Divide the dough into 6 equal parts.

4 Make scones - put 15 g of processed cheese in the middle of the puree. Repeat with all six scones.

5 Put a little oil in a pan and fry for 5 minutes on both sides.

description:
Quick and Easy Piyali Fish Recipe

Ingredients:
 
1. Piyali Fish 200 gm
2. Cooking Oil 3 tbsp
3. Onion 1 cup
4. Coconut Paste ¼ cup
5. Red Chili 1 tsp 
6. Turmeric 1 tsp 
7. Coriander 1 tsp 
8. Salt to taste
9. 2 Lime Leaves
10. 5 green chilies 
11. Fresh Coriander 1 tbsp

Instructions: 

1. In a frying pan, drizzle cooking oil with chopped onion, coconut paste, red chili, turmeric, coriander, salt, and lime leaves.
2. Add piyali fish and mix well. Garnish with green chilies.
3. Cook for 5 minutes on medium heat and garnish with fresh coriander.
4. Cook for another 15 minutes on low heat. 

Ready to Enjoy!

description:
🌮Recipe ￼for Nacho Dip

Ingredients:

2 ounces cream cheese, softened
2 teaspoons Kitcheneez Taco Seasoning
6 ounces shredded Mexican-blend cheese (1 1/2 cups), divided
1 (15 oz) can black beans, drained and rinsed
1 (15 oz) can corn kernels, drained
1 (14.5 oz) can diced tomatoes, drained or 2 ripe tomatoes, chopped
1 (4-ounce) can chopped green chiles
Topping options: diced tomatoes, diced avocado, sour cream, fresh or pickled jalapeños, fresh cilantro leaves
Tortilla chips, for serving

Directions:

Preheat oven to 350*.
Place the cream cheese into a bowl. Add Kitcheneez Taco seasoning and 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese. Mix well.
Add black beans, corn, tomatoes and green chilies. Stir to combine.
Pour into an 8 x 8 baking dish. Spread evently and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20-30 minutes or until heated through then broil for 1-2 minutes until the cheese bubbles. Top with desired toppings and serve with tortilla chips.
Top with desired toppings and serve with tortilla chips.

description:
Haven’t cooked a nice meal for myself at home in so long. It’s been busy and spending the afternoon in the kitchen just hasn’t been an option, or I just haven’t had the energy for it. Honestly, we’ve done more in the last month then we’ve done in the last 3 years it seems! Since coming back from our honeymoon, I’ve slowly been easing myself back to my daily routine and habits, like starting to go on some small runs again, seeing friends, doing the sauna, etc.

Chris is away for the weekend so I decided today was going to be all about me 😈 I spent my Saturday at the market, the library, the beach and the kitchen, and now I’m just about to sit down and have a romantic dinner date with myself 🥰

This is a yam and cherry tomatoes tart with sage and goats cheese. I imagine you can change the produce with the seasons; pumpkin and broccoli for the fall sounds good!

Ingredients:
Pie crust (I had some in my freezer that I’d made earlier)
1 cup ricotta cheese
6 eggs
1 large yam, peeled cubed
1/2 cup sliced cherry tomatoes
Goat cheese, broken into pieces to sprinkle on top
Sage leaves, to sprinkle on top
Salt and pepper

Preheat oven to 400. Roast your yams and bake your crust for 20 minutes or until golden. Place eggs, ricotta, tomatoes and salt and pepper in a bowl, whisk to combine. Remove the crust and yams from the oven, place the yams on the crust then pour mixture overtop. Top egg mixture with goats cheese and sage. Bake for another 25 minutes.
.
.
.
.
.
.

description:
Need some lunch inspiration for the week ahead? ⁣
⁣
Try this very versatile quinoa salad that is nutritious, tasty and can be prepared in less then 10 minutes. Add any seasonal vegetables and whiz up a quick dressing like our famous green dressing or an easy one such as apple cider vinegar, mustard, lemon and olive oil or hummus/ pesto 😋⁣
⁣
I made a large bowl of this that gave me three servings then added in some extra protein such as chicken, boiled eggs, lean meat or beans 😋⁣
⁣
INGREDIENTS: ⁣
⁣
✔️1 cup quinoa, rinsed ⁣
✔️1 capsicum, sliced ⁣
✔️1/2 cucumber, chopped ⁣
✔️1 punnet cherry tomatoes, halved ⁣
✔️1 can organic chickpeas, rinsed and drained ⁣
✔️1 small red onion, sliced finely ⁣
✔️1 spring onion, sliced small bunch of parsley, chopped⁣
✔️1/2 block of feta, crumbled ⁣
⁣
Method: ⁣
⁣
1️⃣ Rinse and drain quinoa then place in a small pot and add 2 cups water. Simmer over medium heat for approx 12-15 mins until cooked. ⁣
2️⃣ Place all the remaining ingredients into a large bowl (except the dressing) and add the cooked quinoa. ⁣
3️⃣ Mix thoroughly then add the dressing and toss to combine.⁣
4️⃣ Serve with your extra source of protein or place in 3-4 containers as your lunch for the week ⁣😋

description:
Butternut squash soup with garbanzo bean. 

Ingredients: 
1 Tbsp olive oil or extra virgin olive oil, plus more for drizzling
1 medium-sized onion, diced
2 garlic cloves, chopped
1 ground turmeric (optional)*
2 cans (15oz-450grams each) chickpeas, rinsed and drained
2 cups (250 grams) squash, cubed
1 (150 grams) medium-sized potato, cubed
3 cups (720 ml) vegetable broth or chicken broth 
1 sprig fresh rosemary (or 1/4 tsp of dried rosemary)
½ tsp salt, or according to your taste
freshly ground black pepper 

I added sautéed spinach, cooked sweet onion, green onion and bacon bits on top along with seasoned garbanzo beans. I seasoned the garbanzo beans with sumac, salt and pepper with a drizzle of EVOO. 

Delish 😋

description:
Chicken Tandoori 

Cut the chicken breast into cubes and the garlic finely.

Place the chicken breast in a bowl with the following ingredients: lemon juice, garlic, curry powder, paprika powder, ground coriander, cumin, chili flakes, grated ginger, pinch of cinnamon, pinch of clove powder and mix.

Add 1 tablespoon of olive oil, the Greek yogurt and salt to taste.
Mix well and let the chicken marinate in the refrigerator (at least 1 hour or longer).

Chop the onion and fry it in a large frying pan with some olive oil.

Then add the marinated chicken and fry until done.
Serve the tandoori chicken with a little Greek yogurt on top or possibly some finely chopped fresh coriander. 

Delicious with a fresh salad or some vegetables and rice and/or naan bread. Enjoy your dinner!

.
A must try rice dish❣️
.
Ingredients:
California Walnuts :  8-10 piece
Onion: 1 sliced
Dried Cranberry : 1 tbsp 
Ghee - 1 tbsp
Pre cooked rice : 1 cup 
Spices salt, turmeric, red chilli powder , black pepper powder . 
Spring onion greens 
Lemon juice 
.

4. Cover for 2 mins on low flame , garnish with spring onion greens and add lemon juice as desired ! 
.

description:
Tomato, garlic and Italian sausage sauce with fresh basil and broccoli 🍅🧄

Fragrant, healthy, quick and satisfying!

Make this vegan or vegetarian by not adding the Italian sausage!

Ingredients: 🥓🫑
-1 red capsicum chopped 
- 1 Italian sausage (spicy or mild) cut into bite sized pieces 
- 2 fresh tomatoes diced
- 1 bunch of basil
-  1 small bunch of broccoli florets 
- 4 garlic cloves finely chopped
- 1 red onion chopped
- 1 jar of red wine and garlic pasta sauce
- Italian herbs mix

Method: 🥦
1. Add a drizzle of olive oil into a pan with the onions and garlic. Fry until translucent.

2. Add tomatoes, capsicums, and broccoli. Add Italian herbs and cook on a low temperature for 20-30 minutes. The longer you cook the richer the flavour develops.

3. Meanwhile in a separate pan, fry the Italian sausage until brown with olive oil. 

3. Then add the pasta sauce and turn the heat down until low to cook for a 5 minutes until the broccoli has softened.

4. Once the vegetables in the sauce have fully cooked- add the Italian sausage and basil leaves. Stir for a few minutes over low heat.

5. Serve with your favourite pasta and Parmesan cheese!

description:
Who knew making a Dhaba style Masala Pav would be this easy 😋
Get your Dhaba curry paste from the link in our bio

Masala Pav Recipe:
Oil - 1 tsp
Cookd Dhaba Curry Paste - 1 Packet
Capsicum (finely chopped) - ½ Cup
Water - 2 tbsp
Pav Bhaji Masala - ½ tsp
Coriander Leaves (finely chopped) - 2 tbsp

Other Ingredients:
Butter - 1 tbsp
Pav - 4 nos
Onion (finely chopped) - ¼ Cup + ½ Cup
Coriander Leaves (finely chopped) - 2 tbsp + 2 tbsp
Grated Cheese
Lemon Wedges - 2 nos (for serving)

Cooking Instructions:

1. Heat oil in a pan and add the Cookd Dhaba curry paste. Saute it for 1 minute to heat it up. 
2. Add capsicum and saute for 2 minutes. 
3. Add water and continue to cook for 2 minutes. 
4. Add coriander leaves and pav bhaji masala & mix. Remove the masala from the pan. 
5. In the same pan, melt some butter. Cut the pav in half horizontally and toast it, with the cut side down. 
6. Turn the pav and toast the other side on low heat. At this point, add some of the prepared masala on one side of the pav. 
7. Add onion, coriander leaves and grated cheese. Cover the pav and remove it from the pan. 
8. Add more masala on top, followed by grated cheese, onion and coriander leaves. Serve with a lemon wedge.

description:
☀️We have another hot and lovely weekend ahead☀️. If you're planning a BBQ my Jewelled Cous Cous is a beautiful and fragrant dish and is perfect to serve with grilled lamb or chicken⁠
⁠
Serves 6 ⁠
⁠
Ingredients:⁠
160g wholemeal cous cous⁠
50ml olive oil⁠
100g pistachio pieces⁠
100g pomegranate seeds⁠
70g dried cranberries⁠
1 teaspoon ground coriander⁠
1 teaspoon ground cumin⁠
1⁄2 teaspoon ground ginger⁠
1⁄2 teaspoon chilli flakes (optional)⁠
1⁄2 teaspoon ground black pepper⁠
⁠
Put the cous cous in a bowl and pour over 300ml of boiling water. Add the oil and leave covered with a tea towel for 5 minutes.⁠
Fork through and stir in the pistachios, cranberries, pomegranate seeds and spices. Add salt to taste.⁠
Serve in your prettiest bowl with lamb chops, a dollop of yoghurt and a crunchy green salad. Enjoy xx

description:
This Hawaiian Macaroni Salad is a magnificent side dish for all the cookouts and picnics or for family dinner night! ✨ 

Save this post! Full recipe below! 👇

Ingredients: 

1/2 lb dry elbow macaroni
1/4 cup onion, minced
2 TB shredded carrots
1 cup real, whole mayo
1/4 cup green onion, thinly sliced
1/2 tsp white pepper
1 tsp kosher salt
Optional: freshly chopped parsley for garnish

Instructions: 

Bring a large pot of well salted water to boil. Cook macaroni until tender, according to package instructions. Drain, rinse thoroughly with cold water; be sure to drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients with the cold, cooked macaroni. Toss to combine well. Chill 2-3 hours or overnight. Toss again right before serving.

description:
Tomato, tomahto! 🍅🍅 It doesn't matter how you say it, all we know is this blistered tomato ravioli recipe is perfecto. Turn your summer harvest into pure perfection with this Blistered Tomato Ravioli Recipe below.

Blistered Tomato Ravioli Recipe
Yield 2 servings
Ingredients:
1 package cheese ravioli
2 pints Wild Harvest organic grape tomatoes
3 cloves garlic, minced
2 tablespoons Wild Harvest organic olive oil
3-4 tablespoons Wild Harvest organic basil, sliced into ribbons
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon pepper

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 400°
2. Place tomatoes in a small bowl and toss with garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper.
3. Lay tomato mixture on a parchment lined baking sheet. Bake for 15-17 minutes or until skins are blistered.
4. While tomatoes are cooking, prepare ravioli according to package instructions.
5. When tomatoes are blistered, remove from oven and add sliced basil. Toss to combine.
6. Top cooked ravioli with tomato basil mixture and additional olive oil if desired.

description:
Pizza Perfection 🍕 ⁣
⁣
These zucchini pizza stacks are truly perfection and super easy to make.  This meal was extra delicious because the zucchini came fresh right from my moms garden.⁣
⁣
 This recipe can be found on the Ww app.  I made some modifications to make it my own.  Check below for ingredients and instructions! ⁣
⁣
Ingredients: ⁣
💙 1 Large Zucchini (+1PP) ⁣
💙 1/2 Cup Fat Free Pizza Sauce (1PP) ⁣
💙 1/2 Ounce Turkey Pepperoni (1PP) ⁣
💙 1 Ounce Trader Joe’s Light Mozzarella (1PP)⁣
⁣
Instructions: ⁣
1. Preheat oven to 425.  Spray muffin pan with cooking spray ⁣
2. In each muffin cup, layer 1 zucchini slice, sauce, and cheese.  Repeat again and layer 1 zucchini slice, sauce and cheese.  This time too with turkey pepperoni slices. ⁣
3. Bake for 18 minutes. ⁣

description:
Whip-It Up Wednesday!

Chicken Bacon Ranch Spaghetti Squash Casserole 😋

ONE recipe your whole family will love & our clients do too. I love healthy recipes that the entire family can enjoy TOGETHER!

Recipe: 
Serves 6

Ingredients:
2 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast, cooked and cubed
4 cups zucchini “noodles” or spaghetti squash
4 slices lean turkey bacon, cooked and chopped up
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 cup unsweetened almond or cashew milk
¾ cup reduced-fat Ranch dressing
2 cups reduced-fat Mexican Cheese blend
1, 4 oz can green chilies

Instructions:
1. Chop your chicken into bits.
2. Mince your garlic cloves.
3. Preheat the oven to 350.
4. Keep a small bit of your bacon drippings in the pan. Cook the garlic cloves (don’t brown). Toss in the chicken and cook for about 1 minute mixing it all together. Dump in the milk and ranch. Mix over medium/low heat for about 2-3 minute until slightly thickened.
5. Add in 1 cup of cheese. Mix EVERYTHING all together thoroughly. Then fold it in with the noodles. Get it all mixed up together. At this point you can add the green Chile and bacon too.
6. Dump the casserole in a large casserole dish. Pour the remaining cup of cheese over the top of the casserole. Cook for 15 minutes at 350 until cheese is nicely melted.

Per serving
1 leaner
1 fat
1 1/2 greens 
1 condiment

To make this a complete lean and green meal, you could always increase the veggies to 6 ½ cups OR serve with a side of another steamed veggie (such as broccoli; ¾ cup per serving needed)

#whipitupwednesday #recipes #healthyrecipes #health #healthcoach #tasty #familymeal #chickenbaconranch

description:
One of the things we talk about often when it comes to healthy eating for those of us over 50 is making sure we get enough protein. 💪

One of the best ways to do that is to find ways to incorporate it into our snacks. 😋 

Today we’re sharing one of our favorite ways to do that: Apple Pie Protein Energy Bites!
The beauty of it is that not only are they good for your body their good for the taste buds too. 

So much so the only real issue is not eating them all in one sitting 

These little delites are only about 45 calories each so you can have 2 or 3 and get a nice does of protein (10-15 grams) as you go about your day. 

Give’em a try and let us know what you think below! 

 🍏 Apple Pie 🍏 Protein Energy Bites (makes about 15) 

 Ingredients:
• 1 cup Apple Pie Filling (Look for No Sugar Added Pie filling)
• 1/4 cup unsweetened cashew milk (or almond)
• 1 tsp powdered Stevia, or to preferred taste
• 1 ½ tsp ground cinnamon, or to preferred taste
• 3/4 cup Vanilla Protein Powder
• 1/4 cup Instant Oats

Directions::
• In a food processor, blend together the apple pie filling, milk, stevia, and cinnamon. Carefully pour in the protein powder and oats, and mix until completely incorporated. 
• Line an airtight container with wax paper or parchment paper.
• Roll the mixture into a ball in your hand and place it in the container.  Ideally you should get about 15 balls. Of course you can make them bigger or small if you choose. 
• Once rolled, transfer the protein ball to an airtight container, and refrigerate until ready to eat! 

Follow us for even more super delish yet healthy recipes!

description:
EASY ORANGE AND CINNAMON WAFFLES 🍊🧇 Who wants to dig in? They make a delicious breakfast, snack, or brunch, and they’re vegan and gluten-free too! 

Ingredients:
1 cup Pancake Waffle Mix Original Iswari
1 cup almond plant-based milk
Zest of 1 orange
1 teaspoon of cinnamon
2 tsp poppy seeds

Preparation:
- Place all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well with the help of a wire rod, until obtaining a homogeneous mass.
- Place small portions of dough in a waffle maker at room temperature medium, and let it cook for about 3 minutes.
- Repeat the process until all the dough is finished.
- Serve with slices of orange, kiwi, and hemp seeds

description:
Over 100 Delicious Vegan recipes. Plant based recipes for muscle growth fat loss and a healthier lifestyle
Visit my website in bio!!!

Squash Blossom Vegan Quesadillas! 🌮

Alexa from @alexafuelednaturally created this incredible dish! Check out her recipe below:

RECIPE
Ingredients:
Corn tortillas
10 squash blossoms
Avocado
Salsa
Salt & pepper

"Tofu cheese"
1 (14 ounces) container medium firm or extra firm tofu
2 tbsp olive oil
Juice of 1 lemon
2 tbsp any plant milk (I used oat milk)
1/2 tsp salt
4 tbsp nutritional yeast (I like Trader Joe's brand)
1/2 tsp garlic powder

Instructions:
1. Remove tofu from package and wrap tofu block in 2 paper towels. Squeeze for 10 seconds then break apart tofu into your food processor. To the food processor add salt, 2 tbsp olive oil, lemon juice, nutritional yeast and garlic powder, plant milk. Pulse 6-10 times until you reach the consistency of ricotta cheese like consistency. Taste and adjust salt and seasonings as needed.

2. Clean off each squash blossom with a damp paper towel then trim the stems. In a pan over medium heat, add a tiny bit of oil and quickly cook the squash blossoms 10 seconds on each side. Season with a little salt and pepper.

3. Warm a cast-iron skillet or pan over medium heat. (Optional tip my mama taught me... wait till pan is super hot then quickly dip tortilla in water and add to hot pan. If the pan Doesn't sizzle then it's not ready!!!* flip the tortilla 10-15 seconds later...This makes your tortillas SO SOFT and fresh tasting giving a dry tortilla the moisture it needs. *** only do this tip w/ corn tortillas not flour tortilla***

4. Add a generous spoonful of tofu cheese on half the tortilla, then add squash blossom then fold over. Let cook for 1 minute on both sides.

5. Add sliced avocados and serve with salsa!

.

🇮🇹Ingredienti: 

1 uovo
40gr ghee
40gr zucchero muscovado
100gr farina di riso integrale
30gr farina di grano saraceno
50gr farina di avena integrale
Cannella
Gocce di cioccolato fondente
Bicarbonato + limone
Ripieno:
Cioccolato fondente 70%

Mischiare l’uovo con il burro ghee. Aggiungere lo zucchero e le farine. Impastare. Aggiungere il bicarbonato con qualche goccia di lime o limone. Impastare. Aggiungere le gocce di cioccolato e impastare fino ad ottenere un panetto omogeneo. Con un cucchiaio di impasto formare un disco. Trasferire su carta da forno. Aggiungere al centro un quadratino di cioccolato fondente. Formare un altro dischetto di pasta e chiudere il biscotto. Continuare a formare i biscotti con il resto dell’impasto. 

Cuocere in forno statico a 180 gradi per 10-13 minuti. 
.
.
.
.

🇬🇧 Ingredients:

1 egg
40g ghee
40g muscovado sugar
100g brown rice flour
30g buckwheat flour
50g wholemeal oat flour
Cinnamon
Dark chocolate chips 
Bicarbonate + lemon
Stuffed:
70% dark chocolate

 
Mix the egg with the ghee butter.  Add the sugar and flour.  Knead.  Add the baking soda with a few drops of lemon.  Knead.  Add the chocolate chips and knead until a homogeneous dough is obtained.  Form a disc with a spoonful of dough.  Transfer to baking paper.  Add a small square of dark chocolate in the center.  Form another disk of dough and close the biscuit.  Continue to form the biscuits with the rest of the dough.

Bake in a static oven at 180 degrees for 10-13 minutes.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

description:
In the words of Bob Ross ~ “we don't make mistakes, just happy little accidents.” 🎨

I needed to make use of some over ripe bananas & came across the banana bread cookies recipe by @mainlymonica on @deliciouslyhealthysweets … I didn’t have a few of the ingredients listed so I altered the recipe and made it my own! Safe to say these banana oaty cookies are my new fave & I’ll be adding them to my morning yoghurt bowl for the foreseeable - the perfect chewy oaty texture, like a flapjack granola!😍

Ingredients:
* 250g ripe banana
* 100g Peanut butter 
* 100g 0% Greek yoghurt 
* 150g @thegreatbritishporridgeco blueberry & banana porridge oats (KG10 for 10% off)
* 80g @freesoulsistas vanilla protein powder 
* 20g maple syrup 
* 1tsp baking powder 

Instructions:
* Preheat oven to 170c & have a lined baking tray set aside
* Mash together banana, peanut butter and yoghurt in a bowl until smooth
* Add in the rest of the ingredients & mix to form a dough (you might need to use your hands)
* Divide dough into balls (50g each) onto the baking tray then flatten into cookies and bake for 20-25mins or until golden!!! mine made 14 cookies! ENJOY!!! 

Cals per cookie: 129kcal
P: 7.8g
F: 5.1g
C: 13.8g

•

description:
If you’re looking for a healthy snack, then we highly recommend snacking on Celery Sticks! Yes, these green stalks are packed with nutrients such as vitamin K & A, potassium, folate and fiber. 

Eating celery means benefiting from its high water content, fiber, and micronutrients. This can lead to improved heart health, diabetes prevention and management, supporting healthy eyesight and weight loss!

Try this delicious recipe

𝗘𝗔𝗦𝗬 𝗕𝗥𝗘𝗘𝗭𝗬 𝗖𝗘𝗟𝗘𝗥𝗬 & 𝗚𝗨𝗔𝗖𝗔𝗠𝗢𝗟𝗘 😋
(makes 8-10 servings)
 
INGREDIENTS:
🔲  24 avocados, chopped
🔲 1 small tomato, seeded and finely chopped
🔲 2 jalapeno peppers (remove seeds for less heat), finely chopped
🔲  2 garlic cloves, finely grated
🔲  ½ cup fresh cilantro, chopped
🔲 ¼ small red onion, finely chopped
🔲 ¼ tsp sea salt
🔲 Celery sticks to dip 
 
1️⃣ Place all ingredients (except the celery sticks) in a bowl and mash together until it reaches the desired consistency. Taste and adjust salt seasoning

2️⃣ Serve with Celery sticks & Enjoy!

description:
A little hearty zesty treat coming your way this recipe wednesday! Today’s Low-carb Pasta with Lemon Chicken features Shirataki Noodles. I mean, lemon chicken?? a little zesty surprise for your meal! Head on down to see the recipe, that’s good for 3!

LOW-CARB PASTA WITH LEMON CHICKEN

INGREDIENTS:

- 2 (200G) packages shirataki noodles
- 1 lb. pastured chicken breast, cut into bite size pieces
- 1 tablespoon MCT Oil or other cooking oil
- 1 large clove organic garlic, minced
- ½ teaspoon dried oregano or 1 teaspoon minced fresh oregano (leaves only)
- ½ teaspoon Himalayan pink salt
- 1 large lemon, zested and juiced (keep zest separate from juice)
- 2 tablespoons grass-fed butter or ghee
- 1 tablespoon Collagelatin, or other grass-fed gelatin
- 1-2 tablespoons fresh oregano to finish (leaves only)

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Prepare shirataki noodles according to package instructions (rinse for 15 seconds, then boil for 2 minutes in a pot of boiling water, then drain the noodles and place them in a dry skillet (no oil) over medium heat and “dry roast” them for 1 minute). Set aside.
2. Heat a large cast iron skillet to medium-high heat and add oil.
3. Add chicken, garlic, dried oregano and Himalayan pink salt to skillet and cook for approximately 8-10 minutes or until fully cooked stirring occasionally. Remove chicken from skillet leaving and set aside.
4. Lower heat under skillet to medium and add lemon juice to deglaze pan. Next add butter and stir until melted. Then whisk in Collagelatin to finish.
5. Add noodles and chicken back to skillet and toss to combine.
6. Serve topped with lemon zest and a garnish of fresh oregano.

→ RECIPE LINK: https://www.bulletproof.com/recipes/low-carb/low-carb-pasta-lemon-chicken-recipe-3g2x/

description:
Kung Pao cauliflower⁣
By @woon.heng 🔥 Perfect over some steamed rice for a delicious meal! Recipe below

⁣Ingredients:⁣
1 small head cauliflower, wash & cut into florets⁣
1 small green bell pepper, cubed⁣
1/2 small red onion, cubed & 2 cloves garlic - sliced⁣
1/4 cup dry roasted cashews⁣
4 dried Thai chilis/red chilis⁣
oil for frying and cooking⁣
⁣
Batter ingredients: Mix 3/4 cup all-purpose flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, a few shakes of white pepper in a bowl with 1 cup of cold water until well combined. The batter should be on the thicker side.
Dip cauliflower florets in batter, shake off excess & fry until golden brown. (I used a small saucepan) Drain excess oil on a paper towel. (Bake version: grease a baking sheet pan with oil, place battered cauliflower florets on the pan. Bake at 485F until light golden brown for about 20-25 mins, be sure to flip halfway & brush a florets with oil, if needed. For the last few minutes, you may broil to get a crispier texture) ⁣Sauce ingredients: Mix together 1/2 tablespoon dark soy sauce, 1/2 tablespoon sugar, 2 tablespoons soy sauce & 1 tablespoon Chinese cooking wine/sherry in a bowl & set aside.⁣
⁣
In a heated nonstick pan with 1 teaspoon oil, sauté onion, garlic, bell pepper, dried chilis until fragrant. Add sauce and cook mixture for 10-15 seconds. Then, add cauliflower florets, cashews, and coat cauliflower well with the sauce. .

.⠀

description:
This Porridge with Pistachio and Chia recipe is a #HubSquad submission from one of our lovely members! It is a warming and spicy whole food-based meal. We suggested increasing the serving size of the oats and milk if you’re after a more filling brekkie – this makes it more aligned to The Plate Model, with 1 serve carbohydrate and 1 serve protein. Adding some fruit such as fresh or frozen berries is also a great way to get a serve of fruit whilst adding a bit of sweetness!

Ingredients:
1 cup oats, rolled
500ml milk, any
1 tbsp chia seeds
½ tsp cardamom seeds
20g pistachios, chopped

Method:
1. Place all ingredients in a pan and bring it to the boil.
2. Reduce the heat and let it simmer for 6-8 minutes, stirring occasionally until the porridge is thick and creamy.
3. Serve as is or top with fresh berries for a serving of fruit. We've topped ours with raspberry compote, which is raspberries, water and 1 tsp sugar simmered over the stove until it thickens.

description:
Grilled seafood🍤🦀💕

Ingredients:
1 clove garlic (chopped) 
1 tbsp olive oil 
1 tbsp lemon juice
1 tbsp soy sauce 
1 tsp cumin
1 tsp turmeric
1 tsp paprika
Pinch of salt

Mix all ingredients together then add the seafood, let it marinate about 10 minutes
Put the seafood onto the skewers
Place skewers on grill for 3 minutes per side untill fully cooked

Serve with white rice, bread or salad 💕

description:
Thai Style salmon.

This recipe is fast and easy and it is also very appetizing.🥰

INGREDIENTS:
- 2 skinless salmon fillets (always go for good quality and not farm one)
- 200gr Thai Jasmine rice
- Chilli flakes, to taste
- Ginger powder, to taste
- 1garlic clove, crushed
- 2 tbsp Miso paste
- 2 tbsp Fish sauce
- 150gr Shiitake mushrooms, sliced
- 250gr pak choi
- 100gr fresh leaf spinach
- 1 lime
- Sesame oil.

METHOD:
Cook the rice in some salted boiling water according to packet instructions.

In a large pan heat the oil (over medium heat), add the chilli, ginger and garlic and cook for a few minutes. Add the Miso paste and fish sauce as well as 300ml of hot water.

Stir and cook for 5 minutes.

Add the salmon and mushrooms, cover, simmer for 10 minutes until the fish is cooked.

Meanwhile steam the pak choi and spinach for 5 minutes approximately.

Serve the salmon with the veggies, the rice and some lime wedges.

#thaisalmon #salmonrecipes #shitakimushrooms #fishrecipes #trytastyflavours #homemadefood #fishmaincourse #healthyrecipes

description:

description:
.
BLUEBERRY & BANANA MUFFINs
by Eat For Wellness

Ingredients: 
4 ripe bananas (mashed)
1 cup fresh or frozen blueberries
1/2 cup Extra Virgin Olive Oil 
2 eggs 
1/4 cup brown sugar 
1 teaspoon bicarb soda
1 ½ teaspoons baking powder 
2 teaspoons cinnamon 
1/3 cup plain natural yoghurt 
1 1/2 cups plain wholemeal flour 
1/3 cup self-raising flour

Method: 
1. Preheat oven to 180°C (160°C fan-forced). Line sixteen 80ml (1/3-cup) capacity muffin tins with paper cases. 
2. In a large bowl, beat sugar and oil with an electric mixer until creamy. Add eggs and beat well.

3.Sift wholemeal flour, self-raising flour, baking powder, bicarb soda and cinnamon in a separate large bowl. 

4.Combine wet ingredients with dry ingredients and fold in the yoghurt, mashed bananas and blueberries. Spoon mixture into lined muffin tins. Bake for 20 minutes or until a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean. Set aside to cool. Serve muffins warm or at room temperature. . 

Created by Vicki Foord (Accredited Practising Dietitian and Sports Dietitian)

Don’t forget to hit the save button 😉

description:

This clafoutis is perfect for summer and so easy to make. Soft and so yummy 🤤 
With a scoop of ice cream or maple syrup on the top this is the perfect combo 😍 
Gluten-free and dairy-free 

Ingredients:

Start by stirring the eggs, the flour and the milk. Then add the honey. Cut the peaches in little pieces.
Put the mixture into a cake mold and add the peaches. 
Bake for 40min at 180°C

description:
A unique and delicious soup that is surely to warm you up on a cool winter night. It’s spicy, creamy and protein-loaded. Spicy Carrot & Peanut Butter Soup is a recipe by Kerry Locatelli. Thanks @nuzest_nz 😍😍😍 

​INGREDIENTS:
​
🍲 1kg Carrots 
🍲 2 Tbsp Avocado Oil or Olive Oil
🍲 1 Onion
🍲 4 Cloves Garlic
🍲 ½ Cup Peanut Butter
🍲 2 Tbsp Kaitaia Fire Chili Sauce
🍲 2 Tbsp Chopped Basil
🍲 1 Serve Just Natural Clean Lean Protein
🍲 1 Litre Vegetable Broth/Stock 
🍲 400ml Coconut Milk
​
​DIRECTION:
​
1. ​Peel and roughly chop the carrots. 
2. Place them in an oven tray, drizzle with 1 tablespoon avocado oil and roast in the oven at 180C for about 30 mins. 
3. Slice and then fry the onion in a large pot with a tablespoon of avocado oil. 
4. Add the garlic and saute. 
5. Once the carrots are roasted, add to the onions and garlic, cover with the vegetable broth and bring to the boil. 
6. Turn the heat down and add the peanut butter, basil and Kaitaia fire. 
7. Allow this to simmer for about 5 mins. 
8. Add the coconut milk and Clean Lean Protein. 
9Blend the soup with a handheld stick blender or carefully in batches in a blender.

​Enjoy!
​
​#SCNATION #healthylifestyle #wellness
#peanutbuttersoup #spicysoup #healthyrecipes #soup #nuzestnz

description:
😉 Take a look at how @eatsimply02 put together her ultimate comfort dish - Cheesy Tomato Fusilli recipe with her favourite Ayam Brand Baked Beans Vegetarian amid the breathtaking scenery of ⛰️ Cradle Mountain. 

😋 Give this recipe a try and you are in for a treat. Remember to tag your vegetarian friend too! 

Ingredients: 
- 425g Ayam Brand Baked Beans - Vegetarian 
- ¼ Zucchini (cut into small cubes)
- 4 big Cherry Tomato (sliced)
- 2 tbsp Parmesan Cheese
- Few dashes Black Pepper
- Few dashes Italian herbs

Preparation: 
1. Add baked beans, zucchini and cherry tomatoes to the cooking pot. Bring it to boil then simmer for 5 minutes. Stir occasionally. (Concurrently, cook fusilli according to instructions.)
2. Stir in parmesan cheese, black pepper and Italian herbs until cheese has melted into the sauce.
3. Pour the sauce onto the fusilli. Serve immediately.

description:
Veggie pasta
🕯 loadshedding friendly 

I love this pasta, I chuck in whatever veggies I have lying around. 

- roast butternut (if electricity)
- slow cook tomatoes / I generally air fry on low heat for a while, alternatively fry on stove top.
- fry lots of garlic in lots of olive oil, towards the end add in chopped broccoli 🥦 be careful not to burn
- (if the kids arent eating I usually add chilli flakes) 
- use whatever veggies you want- spinach is also a goodie.

- cook your pasta
- chuck all your veggies in.
- finely chop a packet of mint and flat leaf parsley, toss in just before serving. 

Dish it up. I like to top with avo and goats cheese. And a swirl of olive oil- But totally optional. 

Key ingredients: lots of olive oil, garlic, mint and parsley. If u have those you good to go 👍🏼🤜🏼

Great served the next day for work lunch too.

description:
Easy Recipe: Rice Pilaf ~ SAVE THIS NOW!

A lot of you asked for the recipe. Here it is. If I can do it, so can you!

Ingredients:
- 3 cups long-grained rice (I’m using basmati), washed and rinsed until clear
- 5 tbsp unsalted butter
- 1 medium onion, minced
- 6 cloves garlic, minced
- 4 1/2 c water
- 1 chicken cube
- 1 tsp ground cumin
- 1 tsp ground turmeric
- 1 cinnamon stick
- 2 tsp salt
- 1/2 tsp pepper
- 1/2 cup dried cranberries
- 1/2 cup pepitas

Steps:
1. Melt the butter on a heavy-set pot like a dutch oven set on medium heat.
2. Add onions until softened. Then add garlic. Cook until a bit golden.
3. Then put in your cumin, turmeric and cinnamon stick. Cook until fragrant.
4. Add in your rice. Stir to make sure the rice is coated with the butter and spice mixture.
5. Pour in your water with the chicken cube. Mix until the chicken cube has melted. 
6. Stir in the salt and pepper. Let it boil.
7. Reduce to low heat. Cover your pot and let it simmer for 15 minutes.
8. Turn off the heat. Add your cranberries and pepitas, cover and let it stand for a few more minutes. Fluff before serving.

description:
COWBOY CAVIAR!
happy tuesday friends😝 It is already august which means summer is coming to an end and the school year is about to begin! I am very excited for my sophomore year of college but also low key dreading all the schoolwork and studying I know is coming my way😬 This summer has been very fun and jam packed with internships, my CNA classes, traveling, and having fun with friends and family. This summer has really given me the opportunity to push myself outside of my comfort zone and explore new things about myself. I realized that I may actually be a city girl and that nursing really is a career I wish to pursue🏙🩺 Let me know one thing you learned about yourself this summer in the comments!
•
*recipe adapted by @spendpennies 
•
INGREDIENTS:
-3 Roma tomatoes seeds removed, diced -⅓ cup red onion diced
-15 oz black beans rinsed and drained
-15 oz black eyed peas rinsed and drained
-1 ½ cups frozen sweet corn thawed 
-1 bell pepper diced  -1 jalapeño pepper seeds removed
•
Dressing:
-⅓ cup olive oil
-2 tablespoons lime juice  -2 tablespoons red wine vinegar
-1 teaspoon sugar
-½ teaspoon salt
-½ teaspoon pepper
-¼ teaspoon garlic powder
•
•
INSTRUCTIONS:
-simply mix all ingredients after chopping the veggies 
-whisk the dressing ingredients together 
-add the dressing to the rest of the ingredients and enjoy!
-eat with tortilla chips, top salads, or just eat as is🥰 
*recipe for store for about 5 days in the fridge!
•
•

description:
LEMON BROCCOLI PASTA 
This is not a pretty picture, but it was gooood! I had this huge bag of broccoli I had to cook, so I needed to make something where broccoli was the main star. I was nervous for this, but my husband loved it!! Indy loved it too minus the broccoli lol. I left it out for her. 

Ingredients: 
Organic Broccoli florets 
@simpletruth4u organic White beans 
Pasta 
Lemon juice 
Optional: bacon, Parmesan cheese 

Instructions: 
Prep broccoli with olive oil, lemon juice and salt.
Roast broccoli in the oven at 400 degrees for 15/20 mins. 
Boil water for pasta. I used @cappellos gluten free.
Drain pasta, but keep about a cup of pasta water in the pot.
Add a cup of lemon juice, salt, a can of rinsed white beans and olive oil to the left over water to make a sauce. 
Add parm cheese to the above if using it.
Add the pasta back in.
Put broccoli on the plate first, then scoop over the pasta mixture so the sauce gets on the broccoli too. 
Add some crumbled bacon on top if you want. You can definitely leave the bacon off. It was still very good w out it. 
Enjoy!

description:
Dhal - a dish made with lentils or other split pulses ⁠
⁠
Probably one of the simplest Indian dishes you  can cook and healthy and cheap too! ⁠
⁠
Lentils are high in fibre, and complex carbohydrates, while low in fat and calories. Their high protein, gluten free whicht makes them a perfect option for those on a low carb diet. ⁠
⁠
This recipe is my go to, and I often change the type of lentils which gives a different texture and flavour to the dish.⁠
⁠
Rayeesa’s Dhal ⁠
⁠
Ingredients:-⁠
⁠
1cup Red split lentils ⁠
½ med onion thinly sliced⁠
2/3 tbsp. ghee (or ½ veg oil + butter) to fry onions ⁠
1 tsp. turmeric ⁠
1tsp. Paprika ⁠
2 tbsp. Garlic and ginger paste⁠
1 ½ tsp Ground coriander ⁠
Salt to taste⁠
Green chillies, 2 small ones chopped (optional)⁠
Fresh coriander to garnish⁠
⁠
Method :-⁠
⁠
Wash lentils thoroughly in clean water⁠
(Leave to soak for ½ hr if possible)⁠
add turmeric and enough water to cover lentils with approx. 1“ above water⁠
Bring to boil and then let it simmer until lentils are cooked and soft.⁠
Get a masher to mash the lentils or a large spoon.⁠
Add 1 cup water, Green chillies, Paprika, Salt, Ground coriander, Garlic & ginger⁠
Let pan simmer for 5-10mins⁠
Gently fry onions in oil & butter until golden brown and add to dhal mixture⁠
Garnish with fresh coriander and serve!⁠
⁠
#dhal #comfortfood

description:
Tagliatelle with a lemon-garlic-zucchini pesto sauce. Light summer lunch.
……………………………………….
Ingredients:
- 1 middle-sized zucchini (enough pesto for two portions)
- tagliatelle pasta
- 1 clove of garlic
- juice of half a lemon 
- pine nuts
- parmesan 
- salt and pepper to season
- olive oil
……………………..
1. Wash and coarsely grate the zucchini. Fry gently in pan with a tablespoon of olive oil and the crushed clove of garlic for five minutes.
2. Cook the tagliatelle according to the packaging.
3. Add the tagliatelle to the zucchini, add the lemon juice and two tablespoons of the pasta water and mix together.
5. Serve with pine nuts and parmesan.

Recipe idea from @bbcgoodfood (without the prawns and with pine nuts and parmesan)

description:
Berry Delicious Vegan Amaranth Breakfast Bowls! Sometimes the simplest breakfast is the best. That can certainly be said of this delicious recipe that takes the creamy smooth texture of cooked amaranth, the super-grain full of fiber and clean nutrition, and couples it with fresh fruit and subtle hints of spice in a coconut milk confection. It's absolute heaven.  It's easy for any day of the week and the amaranth can be cooked in a rice cooker.  Make it ahead and it is a quick re-heat for busy mornings.

Ingredients:

3 cups Water
1 cup Organic Grains Amaranth (http://ow.ly/5TNs50KfrM0)
 1/2 tsp Salt
 2 cups Fresh strawberries
1 cup Fresh blueberries or blackberries
Agave nectar
½ cup Coconut milk
1 tsp Cinnamon
½ tsp Ginger
1-2 Tbsp. Orange zest (1 orange)

Cook the Amaranth

1 cup amaranth
3 cups water
salt to taste (I use about 1 tsp)

Directions:  Combine water and salt in a 1 and a half quart (6 cups) capacity heavy pot with a tight-fitting lid and bring to a boil. Add the grain, cover the pot, and turn the burner to the lowest setting.
Cook covered without stirring for 25 minutes. 

Vegan Breakfast bowls:

To the cooked amaranth pot add ½ cup agave, ½ cup coconut milk, 1 tsp cinnamon, ½ tsp ginger, zest of 1 orange. Divide between 4 bowls. Top each bowl with ½ cup sliced strawberries, ¼ cup blueberries and a drizzle of agave. Enjoy.

#Vegan #breakfast #amaranth #grainbowls #easymeals #organicfood

description:
SAUSAGE, MUSHROOM & BRIE EGG BAKE

INGREDIENTS:
- 16 oz mild Italian sausage
- 2 cups mushroom (sliced)
- 1 small red onion (diced)
- 1 clove minced garlic
- 4 cups spinach
- 1 cup brie cheese (cubed)
- 10 eggs
- 1/2 cup milk
- 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1 1/2 tsp onion powder
- 1 tsp green goddess seasoning (can omit)
- salt
- pepper
- 1 can crescent roll

STEPS:
1. Start by preheating the oven to 350 degrees.  While the oven is preheating, brown the sausage, slice the mushrooms, and dice the onion.
2. Once the sausage is done, set aside and add the mushroom, onion, and garlic to the pan with the grease from the sausage.  Stir frequently until it is all soft and fragrant, then add in the spinach until it is wilted.  Set aside.
3. Next dice up the brie cheese into cubes and also set aside.  Grab a medium sized bowl and add the eggs, milk, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper, and green goddess seasoning.  Mix until well combined.
4. Once everything is has been prepped it’s time to assemble the bake.  Start by adding the crescent roll to the base layer of a 9 x 12 baking dish.  Next follow with the browned sausage, the sautéed veggies, and the brie cheese.  Finally top it all with the egg mixture.
5. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean in the middle.  Serve with avocado and your favorite hot sauce!

Enjoy! ✨

-
this is one of my favourite meals to make at uni because it’s simple and has a lot of flavours! i didn’t take any videos from when i made it so i’m gonna just write everything :(

chicken fillet or thighs (preferred meat) 
avocado
coriander 
corn
black beans 
lime 
paprika/bell peppers
rice 
mayo

description:
Broccoli & Bacon Creamy Pasta 🥦🥓
This meal was so yummy and only took 30 minutes.

Ingredients: 
2 heads Broccoli 
450ml Thickened Cream
3Tbs Vegeta
8 Strips of Streaky Bacon sliced 
Spiral pasta or pasta of your choice
Grated Fresh Parmigiano Reggiano 
2Tsp Paprika 
Chilli flakes optional

Method:
1. Boil your broccoli and pasta both in salted water in seperate pots. Cook your pasta 1-2 min under the recommended time as we will finish it in the sauce.
2. Grate your parmesan and slice your bacon while the broccoli boils.
3. Fry off your bacon in a pot till the fat renders and it crisps up on the edges, season with salt and pepper ( don’t drain the fat it help will season the sauce )
4. Remove your broccoli from the water and cut how you like, I liked small florets for this dish, then add it to the pot with the bacon and fry off for a minute. Then add a few tablespoons of pasta water along with your Parmigiano till it melts.
5. Add your thickened cream to the pot, I did about 450ml for 3 servings. I then add salt, pepper, paprika, & vegeta chicken seasoning.
6. Add your drained pasta to the sauce pot and mix well, let everything cook together till your pasta has finished cooking.
7. Serve with chilli flakes & extra parm on top ☺️🫶🏼

#cooking #pastarecipe #easymeals

INGREDIENTS:

3 large zucchini, trimmed (about 4 pounds), sliced lengthwise into 24 ⅛-inch-thick strips

Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper

1 tablespoon olive oil

3/4 pound ground Italian sausage, casing removed

1 cup part skim ricotta cheese

1/3 cup freshly grated Parmesan

1 large egg

1/4 cup chopped fresh basil leaves

2 cloves garlic, minced

1 1/2 cups marinara sauce, divided

2 cups shredded mozzarella, divided

DIRECTIONS:

Line a baking sheet with paper towels. Lay zucchini slices flat in a single layer onto the prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle each side with 1/4 teaspoon salt; let stand 15 minutes.

Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add Italian sausage and cook until browned, about 3-5 minutes, making sure to crumble the sausage as it cooks; drain excess fat.

In a medium bowl, combine sausage, ricotta, Parmesan, egg, basil and garlic; season with salt and pepper, to taste.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.

Spread 1 cup marinara sauce sauce onto the bottom of a 1o-inch oven-proof skillet; set aside.
